This folder contains the necessary files to run the ABC algorithm using CosmoABC. 

documentation available at http://cosmoabc.readthedocs.io/en/latest/


User input file:  toy_model.input
functions file:   toy_model_funtions.py

The summary statistics used in this simple example is the following:
 - given a simulated dataset d1 and an observed dataset d2
 - do a linear fit for d1, resulting in parameters (a1,b1) 
 - do a linear fir for d2, resulting in parameters (a2,b2)
 - return sqrt((a1-a2) **2 + (b1-b2) ** 2)

at this point this is a sufficient summary statistics because we know the model is linear. 
With time this must be made more realistic.

In order to run the ABC code just clone the github repository (pip version will be updated soon)
https://github.com/COINtoolbox/CosmoABC

inside the cosmoabc folder do, in the command line
>> python setup.py install

return to this directory and test the distance definition
>> test_ABC_distance.py -i toy_model.input -f toy_model_functions.py

Run the ABC analysis
>> run_ABC.py -i toy_model.input -f toy_model_functions.py
